LPF_orde2_time_10Hz = pd.read_csv("CSV/LPF_Orde2_10Hz.csv")
LPF_orde2_time_100Hz = pd.read_csv("CSV/LPF_Orde2_100Hz.csv")

3.1.1 a) Butterworth¶

In [3]:
# 10 Hz -----------------------------------
Vout_peak = float(LPF_orde2_time_10Hz["butter_2"].max())

plt.figure(1) 
plt.plot(
    LPF_orde2_time_10Hz["TIME"], LPF_orde2_time_10Hz["Vin"],
)
plt.plot(
    LPF_orde2_time_10Hz["TIME"], LPF_orde2_time_10Hz["butter_2"],
    linestyle = "--"
)
plt.axhline(y = Vout_peak, linestyle = ":", color = "red")
plt.title(r"Butterworth $2^{nd}$ Order $(F ~=~ 10 ~Hz$)")
plt.xlabel("Time (s)")
plt.ylabel("Voltage (V)")
plt.legend([
    "Vin",
    "Vout",
    f"Peak = {Vout_peak:.2f} V"
])
plt.grid(True, which="Both")


# 100 Hz ----------------------------------
Vout_peak = float(LPF_orde2_time_100Hz["butter_2"].max())

plt.figure(2) 
plt.plot(
    np.array(LPF_orde2_time_100Hz["TIME"]) * 1000, LPF_orde2_time_100Hz["Vin"],
)
plt.plot(
    np.array(LPF_orde2_time_100Hz["TIME"]) * 1000, LPF_orde2_time_100Hz["butter_2"],
    linestyle = "--"
)
plt.axhline(y = Vout_peak, linestyle = ":", color = "red")
plt.title(r"Butterworth $2^{nd}$ Order $(F ~=~ 100 ~Hz$)")
plt.xlabel("Time (ms)")
plt.ylabel("Voltage (V)")
plt.legend([
    "Vin",
    "Vout",
    f"Peak = {Vout_peak:.2f} V"
])
plt.grid(True, which="Both")

FREQ Butter_2 Bessel_2 Cheby_2

In [8]:
plt.figure(1)
plt.plot(LPF_orde2_freq["FREQ"], LPF_orde2_freq["Butter_2"], color = "#ff0000")
plt.axvline(x=1000, linestyle=":", label="Fc", color="#ff0000")
plt.legend([
    "Butterworth",
    "3dB point"
])
plt.xscale("log")
plt.ylabel("Gain (dB)")
plt.title(r"Butterworth $2^{nd}$ Order ( $F_c = 1000 ~Hz$ )")

plt.axvline(x=1000, linestyle=":", label="Fc", color="#ff0000")
plt.grid(True, which="both")

# Bessel

plt.legend([
    "Bessel",
    "3dB point"
])
plt.xscale("log")
plt.title(r"Bessel $2^{nd}$ Order ( $F_c = 1000 ~Hz$ )")
plt.ylabel("Gain (dB)")
plt.xlabel("Frequency (Hz)")
plt.grid(True, which="both")

# Chebychev 3-dB ripple
plt.figure(3)
plt.plot(LPF_orde2_freq["FREQ"], LPF_orde2_freq["Cheby_2"], color="#0000ff")
plt.axvline(x=1000, linestyle=":", label="Fc", color="#ff0000")
plt.legend([
    "Cheby",
    "3dB point"
])
plt.xscale("log")
plt.title(r"Cheby 3-dB $2^{nd}$ Order ( $F_c = 1000 ~Hz$ )")
plt.ylabel("Gain (dB)")
plt.xlabel("Frequency (Hz)")
plt.grid(True, which="both")

# Comparison
plt.figure(4)
plt.plot(
    LPF_orde2_freq["FREQ"], LPF_orde2_freq["Butter_2"],
    LPF_orde2_freq["FREQ"], LPF_orde2_freq["Bessel_2"],
    LPF_orde2_freq["FREQ"], LPF_orde2_freq["Cheby_2"],
)
plt.axvline(x=1000, linestyle=":", label="Fc", color="#ff0000")
plt.legend([
    "Butterworth",
    "Bessel",
    "Chebychev",
    "3dB point"
])
plt.xscale("log")
plt.title(r"$2^{nd}$ Order Lowpass Filter Comparison ( $F_c = 1000 ~Hz$ )")
plt.ylabel("Gain (dB)")
plt.xlabel("Frequency (Hz)")
plt.grid(True, which="both")

plt.show()

3.1.3 a) Kondisi Sinyal Pada -40 dB (Butterworth)¶

In [11]:
LPF_orde2_40dB = pd.read_csv("CSV/LPF_Orde2_Butter_40dB_Time.csv")
In [12]:
plt.figure(1)
plt.plot(
    np.array(LPF_orde2_40dB["TIME"]) * 1000000, LPF_orde2_40dB["Vin"],
    np.array(LPF_orde2_40dB["TIME"]) * 1000000, LPF_orde2_40dB["Butter_2"],
)
plt.title(r"Butterworth ; $F_{in}$ = 10 kHz ; Gain = -40 dB")
plt.xlabel(r"Time ($us$)")
plt.ylabel("Voltage (V)")
plt.legend([
    "Vin",
    "Vout",
])
plt.grid(True, which = "both")


# ZOOMED IN -----------------------------
# Getting vout peak after settling time
subset_data = LPF_orde2_40dB[
    LPF_orde2_40dB["TIME"] * 1000000 > 800
]
subset_data = subset_data[["TIME", "Butter_2"]]
Vout_peak = float(subset_data["Butter_2"].max())

plt.figure(2)
plt.plot(
    np.array(LPF_orde2_40dB["TIME"]) * 1000000, LPF_orde2_40dB["Butter_2"],
    color = "orange"
)
plt.axhline(y = Vout_peak, linestyle = ":", color = "red")
plt.title(r"Zoom in $V_{OUT}$")
plt.xlabel(r"Time ($us$)")
plt.ylabel("Voltage (V)")
plt.legend([
    "Vout",
    f"Peak = {Vout_peak:.4f} V"
])
plt.grid(True, which = "both")

plt.show()

3.1.3 b) Kondisi Sinyal Pada -40dB (Bessel)¶

Untuk Bessel & Chebychev, pemrosesan sedikit berbeda di awal, karena mempunyai settling time lebih lama. Untuk mendapatkan nilai peak (max) yang akurat, datanya harus di subset agar data yang diambil hanya saat mendekati settling time saja.

In [13]:
LPF_orde2_40dB = pd.read_csv("CSV/LPF_Orde2_10000Hz.csv")
In [14]:
plt.figure(1)
plt.plot(
    np.array(LPF_orde2_40dB["TIME"]) * 1000000, LPF_orde2_40dB["Vin"],
    np.array(LPF_orde2_40dB["TIME"]) * 1000000, LPF_orde2_40dB["Bessel_2"],
)
plt.title(r"Bessel ; $F_{in}$ = 10 kHz ; Gain = -40 dB")
plt.xlabel(r"Time ($us$)")
plt.ylabel("Voltage (V)")
plt.legend([
    "Vin",
    "Vout",
])
plt.grid(True, which = "both")


# ZOOMED IN -----------------------------
# Getting vout peak after settling time
subset_data = LPF_orde2_40dB[
    LPF_orde2_40dB["TIME"] * 1000000 > 800
]
subset_data = subset_data[["TIME", "Bessel_2"]]
Vout_peak = float(subset_data["Bessel_2"].max())

plt.figure(2)
plt.plot(
    np.array(LPF_orde2_40dB["TIME"]) * 1000000, LPF_orde2_40dB["Bessel_2"],
    color = "orange"
)
plt.axhline(y = Vout_peak, linestyle = ":", color = "red")
plt.title(r"Zoom in $V_{OUT}$")
plt.xlabel(r"Time ($us$)")
plt.ylabel("Voltage (V)")
plt.legend([
    "Vout",
    f"Peak = {Vout_peak:.4f} V"
])
plt.grid(True, which = "both")

plt.show()

plt.grid(True, which="both")

plt.show()

Melalui grafik tersebut, dapat dilihat bahwa ripple-nya menuju nilai minus. Sehingga fungsi yang digunakan untuk mencari adalah .min(), dengan range pencarian dari 10 Hz - 999 Hz.

In [24]:
subset_data = LPF_orde3_freq[
    LPF_orde3_freq["FREQ"] < 1000
]
subset_data = subset_data[["FREQ", "Cheby_3"]]

# Ripple value
ripple = float(subset_data["Cheby_3"].min())

# Max ripple at frequency:
ripple_freq = LPF_orde3_freq[
    LPF_orde3_freq["Cheby_3"] == ripple
]
ripple_freq = float(ripple_freq["FREQ"])

# Plotting ulang dengan horizontal line
plt.figure(1, figsize = (12,12))
plt.plot(LPF_orde3_freq["FREQ"], LPF_orde3_freq["Cheby_3"], color="#0000ff")
plt.axvline(x=1000, linestyle=":", color="orange")

# Ripple line indicator
plt.axvline(x=ripple_freq, linestyle=":", color="red")
plt.axhline(y=ripple, linestyle = ":", color = "green")

plt.legend([
    "Cheby",
    "Cutoff",
    f"Ripple = {ripple} dB",
    f"Ripple freq = {ripple_freq} Hz"
], loc = "lower right")
plt.xscale("log")
plt.title(r"Cheby 3-dB $3^{rd}$ Order ( $F_c = 1000 ~Hz$ )")
plt.ylabel("Gain (dB)")
plt.xlabel("Frequency (Hz)")
plt.grid(True, which="both")

plt.show()
